REASONING: According to the CIA World Factbook 2024 data, Singapore ranks #1 in Real GDP per capita (PPP) at $132,600, ahead of Luxembourg at $128,200
However, Wikipedia's list of countries by nominal GDP per capita shows different rankings, with Monaco at $256,581, Liechtenstein at $207,973, and Luxembourg at $140,941 in the top positions
The discrepancy comes from different measurement methods - Real GDP (PPP) adjusts for purchasing power parity and cost of living differences, while nominal GDP per capita uses current exchange rates

Singapore does appear to rank #1 in Real GDP per capita (PPP) according to CIA data, but not in nominal GDP per capita rankings where it would be significantly lower than Monaco, Liechtenstein, and Luxembourg
The claim is partially true depending on the measurement method used - Singapore has the highest Real GDP per capita (PPP) but not the highest nominal GDP per capita
